[2] USA (Wisconsin)
Date: Tue 12 Dec 2017
Source: Marshfield News Herald [edited]
http://www.marshfieldnewsherald.com/story/news/2017/12/12/whooping-cough-forces-neillsville-cancel-sports-after-school-activities/945934001/


All athletic contests and activities that require contact outside the Neillsville School District have been canceled until Monday [11 Dec 2017] because of several cases of whooping cough, according to school officials.

In late November [2017], a family in the district with a child in the elementary school and another child in the 7th through 12th grades tested positive for pertussis, commonly known as whooping cough, said John Gaier, Neillsville School District administrator.

As of Tuesday [12 Dec 2017], the Clark County Health Department had confirmed 5 families with whooping cough, Gaier said. On the recommendation of the Health Department, the school canceled all athletic contests and other activities that would expose students in other counties or school districts to Neillsville School District students, Gaier said. Athletics are most affected, with a couple of field trips also canceled.

The Clark County Health Department also advised the school district not to cancel classes, stating students would be better off at school than congregating at home, Gaier said. The district will monitor students for symptoms of whooping cough, he said.

[Byline: Karen Madden]

--
