[3] USA (Washington)
Date: 12 Dec 2017
Source: KATU [edited]
http://katu.com/news/local/whooping-cough-hits-mountain-view-high-school-in-vancouver


Whooping cough has made its way into a Vancouver high school, sending some kids home sick. There have been 6 confirmed cases of pertussis at Mountain View High School according to KATU's news partner, The Columbian.

There was an outbreak in Clark County in 2015 with several hundred reported cases. According to Clark County Public Health's website, those infected can't return to school until they complete a 5-day course of antibiotics. Public health officials strongly encourage parents to vaccinate their kids as the best defense.

[Byline: Jackie Labrecque]

--
