[Last month (November 2017) Henderson County reported 8 cases in students with whooping cough at 5 schools (ProMED-mail post Pertussis (11): USA, Australia, New Zealand, Canada 20171203.5479380); now the total is 21 cases. Henderson County, with a population of 106 740 residents in 2010, is located in the Blue Ridge Mountains of the southwestern part of the U.S. state of North Carolina; its county seat is Hendersonville (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Henderson_County,_North_Carolina). A map showing the location of Henderson County can be found at: https://www.google.com/maps/place/Henderson+County,+NC. - Mod.ML]

